    "body": "## Summary\n\nFollow-up to #22814. This makes the CUDA GroupNorm+SiLU VAE fast path the default instead of requiring an environment variable.\n\nChanges are intentionally narrow:\n- remove the `SGLANG_USE_CUDA_HUNYUANVIDEO_GROUP_NORM_SILU` gate\n- add a small `apply_group_norm_silu` helper with safe fallbacks for CPU, grad-enabled, non-SiLU, non-affine, or inplace activation cases\n- route HunyuanVideo VAE ResBlock and encoder/decoder output GroupNorm+SiLU pairs through the helper\n- keep the Triton op guarded against grad-enabled execution\n- update the CUDA unit test to exercise the default helper without importing the Hunyuan VAE module\n\n## Impact\n\nHunyuanVideo VAE decode now uses the fused GroupNorm+SiLU path by default when the existing Triton kernel supports the input. Unsupported cases keep the original PyTorch `activation(norm(x))` behavior.\n\n## Validation\n\n- `python3 -m py_compile python/sglang/jit_kernel/diffusion/group_norm_silu.py python/sglang/jit_kernel/diffusion/triton/group_norm_silu.py python/sglang/jit_kernel/tests/diffusion/test_group_norm_silu.py python/sglang/multimodal_gen/envs.py python/sglang/multimodal_gen/runtime/models/vaes/hunyuanvae.py`\n- `python3 -m ruff check python/sglang/jit_kernel/diffusion/group_norm_silu.py python/sglang/jit_kernel/diffusion/triton/group_norm_silu.py python/sglang/jit_kernel/tests/diffusion/test_group_norm_silu.py python/sglang/multimodal_gen/envs.py python/sglang/multimodal_gen/runtime/models/vaes/hunyuanvae.py`\n- `git diff --check`\n- H100 GPU 0: `pytest -q python/sglang/jit_kernel/tests/diffusion/test_group_norm_silu.py -q` -> 14 passed\n\nHunyuanVideo model benchmark from `sglang-diffusion-benchmark-profile` after clearing GPU processes:\n\n| Variant | E2E | Denoising | Decoding | Peak memory |\n| --- | ---: | ---: | ---: | ---: |\n| baseline, no fuse | 63310.42 ms | 46274.60 ms | 16726.66 ms | 49446 MB |\n| fuse default | 60472.53 ms | 46241.21 ms | 13914.22 ms | 49446 MB |\n| delta | -2837.90 ms (-4.5%) | -33.39 ms (-0.1%) | -2812.44 ms (-16.8%) | 0 MB |\n\nI did not use LTX-2 as model-level proof because the cached LTX-2 audio VAE config uses `norm_type: pixel`, so it does not hit this GroupNorm+SiLU fuse path.\n",
